        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1182619" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1418610910063897671"><br/>A masterpiece, demonstrating how grace redeems and love restores over time. <br/><br/>This play features one of Shakespeare&apos;s most interesting psychological studies (Leontes) and two of his most charming heroines (Hermione and Perdita). Shakespeare&apos;s art has deepened to the point where he can deliberately choose an outrageously improbable denouement and present it in a way that makes his play more moving and richer symbolically than it would have been with a more probable conclusion.</span>
  <span id="freeText1418610910063897671" style="display:none"><br />A masterpiece, demonstrating how grace redeems and love restores over time. <br /><br />This play features one of Shakespeare's most interesting psychological studies (Leontes) and two of his most charming heroines (Hermione and Perdita). Shakespeare's art has deepened to the point where he can deliberately choose an outrageously improbable denouement and present it in a way that makes his play more moving and richer symbolically than it would have been with a more probable conclusion.</span>
