<div id="review_1773679489" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1773679489" />
    <a title="Michael Finocchiaro" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48483884-michael-finocchiaro"><img alt="Michael Finocchiaro" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576692048p2/48483884.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1773679489?book_show_action=true">Oct 02, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Finocchiaro" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Finocchiaro" href="/user/show/48483884-michael-finocchiaro">Michael Finocchiaro</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=romances">romances</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=english-16th-c">english-16th-c</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=theatre">theatre</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=shakespeare">shakespeare</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1773679489" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13004789036748762964">This is a beautiful Shakespearean play with naturalistic elements typical of his later period. The now-infamous name of Hermione from this play likely acted as an inspiration to Rowling from the heroine of this play who is reborn at the end. There are elements of comedy and tragedy here as well as an interesting personification of time. One of the better romances!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

