  <span id="freeText10576474416338412883" style="display:none"><i>“It is an heretic that makes the fire, <br />Not she which burns in’t.”</i><br /><br />This story of a jealous king who imprisons his wife and exiles his daughter was very disappointing. I was hoping for some winter warmth, but instead, I found a grey and bleak and lifeless tale. In the absence of a helpful teacher or seeing a brilliant performance, I rely on Shakespeare’s sparkling lines to carry me through the bumpy spots of his plays. Unfortunately, except for the above quote, I didn’t find those here, so there was sadly nothing much for me in this one.<br /></span>
